r King of Abyssinia","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 5, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, told us about the Negus, the ruler of Abyssinia, on the day he died. The Prophet said to us, \u201cSeek forgiveness for your brother.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1263, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 951 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":21382,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2015\/12\/22\/janazah-stand-funeral-respect\/","url_meta":{"origin":662,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Janazah: Stand up for funerals respectfully","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 22, 2015","format":false,"excerpt":"'Amir ibn Rabi'ah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen you see a funeral procession, stand up for it until it passes or the deceased is placed in the grave.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1245, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 958 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi (authenticity agreed upon) according\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":34665,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/12\/07\/prophet-buries-a-hypocrite\/","url_meta":{"origin":662,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Funerals: The Prophet respectfully buries a hypocrite","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 7, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Jabir ibn Abdullah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, came to the hypocrite Abdullah ibn \u2018Ubayy after he was placed in his grave. The Prophet ordered him to be taken out, he placed him on his knees, he blew his blessed breath over him, and\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25340,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/10\/26\/one-relieved-and-relieved-from\/","url_meta":{"origin":662,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Death: One is relieved, and one is relieved from","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 26, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Qatadah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, passed by a funeral and he said, \u201cOne is relieved and one is relieved from.\u201d They said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, what is one relieved and one relieved from?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cThe believing servant is relieved\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37529,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/12\/15\/4-takbeer-salat-janazah\/","url_meta":{"origin":662,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Janazah: Four takbirat in the funeral prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 15, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings upon him, announced the news to people on the day the Negus died. The Prophet went out with them to the place of prayer, they stood in rows, and he exalted Allah with four exaltations. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1333, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/662","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=662"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/662\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=662"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=662"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=662"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}